Stocks in Europe Advance, Rebounding From Biggest Decline for Four Weeks

-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 
2011-04-13T07:02:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/stocks-in-europe-advance-rebounding-from-biggest-decline-for-four-weeks.html
European stocks gained, rebounding
from the biggest drop in four weeks, before reports that may
show European factory orders and American retail sales
increased. U.S. index futures and Asian shares advanced.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index rose 0.3 percent to 277.19 at
8:01 a.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  